Version 10 - 2024-01-17
    Added benchmarking.
    The BLAKE3 digest size must be between 32 and 256, where 256 produces a 512-byte output, the maximum password size supported by cryptsetup.

Version 9 - 2024-01-17
    Minor fixes.

Version 8 - 2024-01-17

    Added Makefile for streamlined builds.
    Performed miscellaneous cleanup tasks.

Version 7 - 2024-01-15

    Set minimum digest size to 64 and maximum digest size to 512.
    (Note: The maximum is currently constrained by the cryptsetup maximum password size)

Version 6 - 2024-01-14

    Prevented newline (\n) characters from being sent with passwords.

Version 5 - 2024-01-11

    Integrated cryptdisks functions.
    Added Plymouth integration.

Version 4 - 2024-01-10

    Removed b3sum due to impracticality with high PIM numbers.
    Developed the initial hasher implementation in C.

Version 3 - 2024-01-09

    Applied minor fixes and improvements.

Version 2 - 2024-01-08

    Deprecated Python version due to incompatibility with root volumes.
    Developed the initial implementation in Dash using b3sum.

Version 1 - 2024-01-06

    Created the initial implementation in Python.
